  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Re-Imagining Class,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2024, explores contemporary socio-economic classifications and their impacts on society. Although it has yet to generate formal citations or online discourse, the work is positioned within a relevant scholarly framework that addresses sustainability and policy implications. The book aims to contribute substantially to discussions around class dynamics in modern societies.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Re-Imagining Class\" presents a timely examination of socio-economic class structures, focusing on their relevance in today's world. Released by Leuven University Press, the book is anticipated to resonate with academics and practitioners alike as it addresses pressing themes that align with sustainable development goals. The work's framing suggests a significant engagement with contemporary debates surrounding class and equity.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While currently lacking citations or external online references, the absence of metrics does not detract from the potential implications of the book. Its strongest signal, inferred from the metadata, is its potential relevance to policy sustainability, scoring a notable 0.55 on the strength of this association. This situates the work as a critical resource for those involved in policy-making and educational reforms related to class structures.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's conceptual foundations and its focus on areas ripe for discussion enable it to contribute to the larger dialogue about class, particularly in academic settings. The anticipated interest from key institutions and scholars, while not yet quantified, suggests an emerging footprint that may evolve as the discourse around the themes presented grows.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As \"Re-Imagining Class\" enters the scholarly landscape, its authors may seek to foster dialogue and invite commentary from both academic and policy circles. The proactive engagement in dissemination through platforms associated with the publisher could further enhance its visibility and impact in addressing contemporary socio-economic issues.</p>",
